messages.content:
You are evaluating whether a technical specification document is relevant to answer a question.

Question: What machine learning models are used in the 3D scanning SDK and what are their performance characteristics?

Document Structure:
{
  "title": "Photorealistic 3D Scanning SDK - Technical Specification",
  "sections": [
    {
      "title": "Feature Detection System",
      "summary": "Detects and matches distinctive features across multiple images using deep learning-based feature detection (SuperPoint) and neural network feature matching (SuperGlue). RANSAC-based outlier rejection and sub-pixel refinement are included.",
      "keywords": ["SuperPoint", "SuperGlue", "FeatureDetectionSystem", "Core ML", "RANSAC"]
    },
    {
      "title": "AI Enhancement Engine",
      "summary": "Enhances reconstruction quality using neural networks for edge detection and refinement, plane fitting and surface reconstruction, measurement enhancement, and error correction.",
      "keywords": ["Edge Detection CNN", "Plane Fitting Network", "Measurement Refinement", "neural networks"]
    },
    {
      "title": "Measurement Extraction System",
      "summary": "Extracts precise measurements from 3D reconstruction with automatic object detection (doors, windows, etc.), dimension extraction, distance measurement, and accuracy estimation.",
      "keywords": ["Object Detection", "YOLO", "Measurement Refinement", "door detection", "window detection"]
    },
    {
      "title": "Performance Requirements",
      "summary": "Defines performance targets for processing time (< 2 min total), memory usage (< 2GB peak), and accuracy (±2mm for measurements).",
      "keywords": ["processing time", "memory usage", "accuracy", "performance targets"]
    },
    {
      "title": "Technical Challenges & Solutions",
      "summary": "Addresses challenges including feature detection in low-texture areas, lighting variations, memory management, real-time performance, and accuracy vs. speed trade-offs.",
      "keywords": ["feature detection", "lighting normalization", "memory management", "GPU acceleration"]
    }
  ]
}

Evaluate relevance by:
1. Matching question terms to document keywords
2. Assessing if section summaries address the question topic
3. Considering if the document domain (database/API/security) matches question domain

Response format:
{
  "relevance_score": <0.0 to 1.0>,
  "reasoning": "<2-3 sentence explanation citing specific sections or keywords>",
  "matching_sections": ["section titles that are most relevant"]
}

Return only valid JSON.
